knowledge: Jupiter (mythology) . Jupiter (from or "Iuppiter" , *djous “day, sky” + *patēr “father," thus "heavenly father"), also known as Jove gen. "Iovis" ), is the god of the sky and thunder and king of the gods in Ancient Roman religion and mythology. Jupiter was the chief deity of Roman state religion throughout the Republican and Imperial eras, until Christianity became the dominant religion of the Empire.
